{
  "texts": [
    "We then extract the short-time temporal envelopes in each band and frame, denoted X j, m and Y j, m, where X j, m = [X j (m -N + 1), X j (m -N + 2), …, X j (m)] T, with N = 30.",
    "The STOI+ metric is the average of the PCC d j, m between X j, m and Y j, m, overall j and m (ref. 26):",
    "We use the negative of the STOI+ metric as the STOI loss:",
    "where J and M are the total numbers of frequency bins (J = 15) and frames, respectively.",
    "Note that L STOI is differentiable with respect to Ŝ t (f), and thus can be used to update the model parameters generating the predicted spectrogram Ŝ t (f)."
  ]
}